{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Vg6SNewd4rjWGYrY7ddqno","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent. I now have all the information you requested. Here's my comprehensive report:\n\n## Codebase Overview Report\n\n### 1. Package.json Scripts\n```json\n{\n  \"predev\": \"tsx scripts/migrate.ts\",\n  \"dev\": \"concurrently -n CH,NEXT -c cyan,green \\\"./clickhouse server -- --path=.clickhouse\\\" \\\"next dev\\\"\",\n  \"build\": \"next build\",\n  \"start\": \"next start\",\n  \"migrate\": \"tsx scripts/migrate.ts\",\n  \"lint\": \"biome check\",\n  \"lint:fix\": \"biome check --fix\",\n  \"test\": \"vitest run\",\n  \"typecheck\": \"tsc --noEmit\"\n}\n```\n\n### 2. Vitest Configuration\n**File:** `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/vitest.config.ts`\n```typescript\nimport path from \"node:path\";\nimport { defaultExclude, defineConfig } from \"vitest/config\";\n\nexport default defineConfig({\n  test: {\n    environment: \"node\",\n    exclude: [...defaultExclude, \"playwright_tests/**/*.spec.ts\"],\n  },\n  resolve: {\n    alias: { \"@\": path.resolve(__dirname, \"src\") },\n  },\n});\n```\n\n### 3. src/lib/identity.ts (Complete)\n**Full content provided above** — Key exports:\n- **`EventRow`** interface: event_id, event_name, timestamp, device_id, user_id, properties, ingested_at, resolved_id\n- **`QueryEventsOptions`** interface: event_name, resolved_id, before (ISO cursor), limit (max 200)\n- **`queryEventsWithResolvedId(options, client)`**: Returns events with resolved_id computed as `coalesce(e.user_id, m.user_id, e.device_id)`. Supports filtering by event_name, resolved_id, and before cursor. Defaults to limit 50.\n- **`getEventsByResolvedId(resolved_id, client)`**: Convenience wrapper returning all events (up to 200) for a resolved identity.\n- **`insertEvent(input, client)`**: Validates, timestamps, inserts event, and handles identity mapping. Throws IdentityConflictError