ved_id filters\n- **Completed:** F1-F6 (ClickHouse client, migrations, dev setup, identity resolution, POST /api/events, POST /api/events/batch)\n\n### 8. MEMORY.md\nDoes not exist at project root.\n\n---\n\n## Key Takeaways for Implementation\n\n1. **Testing pattern:** Use `vi.hoisted()` for mock setup, mock at module level before imports, and create hoisted error classes for instanceof checks\n2. **Route pattern:** Parse JSON, handle errors with appropriate HTTP status codes, return JSON responses\n3. **Type exports:** Identity.ts provides all core types and functions; QueryEventsOptions already supports pagination params (before cursor, limit)\n4. **Error handling:** IdentityConflictError has status property; other errors are generic Error instances\n5. **CLI commands:** `npm test`, `npm run lint`, `npm run typecheck`, `npm run build`"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8abfa75e-8428-4312-86e7-bde2aa8c0983","uuid":"0c080aaa-02d7-492b-b60c-23d0d9fb5e45","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:37:54.724Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the current state of this Next.js/TypeScript codebase before implementing a new feature. Please explore the following and report back:\n\n1. Read `package.json` — find test, lint, build, and typecheck commands\n2. Read `vitest.config.*` or any test config files\n3. Read `src/lib/identity.ts` — especially `queryEventsWithResolvedId`, `EventRow`, `QueryEventsOptions` exports\n4. Read `src/lib/clickhouse.ts`\n5. Look at existing API route files — specifically `src/app/api/events/route.ts` and `src/app/api/events/batch/route.ts` for patterns\n6. Look at existing test files — find any route test files that mock modules (look in `src/app/api/events/` or nearby `__tests__` dirs) to understand testing conventions\n7. Check `features/status.md` for context on what's been completed\n8. Check if `MEMORY.md` exists at the project root\n\nReport the full content of: identity.ts, one existing route test file (i